.TH "netdev_set_mac_address" 9 "netdev_set_mac_address" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
netdev_set_mac_address \- set network device MAC address
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" netdev_set_mac_address
.BI "(struct net_device *dev "  ","
.BI "void *addr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Network device.
.IP "addr" 12
Buffer of MAC address.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is used to set the MAC address of the network device.

Return 0 to indicate success.
